{
  "stem": "22734.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- but whatever he gave to his mother, she kept some of it for him, because she knew his plan.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He decided he will not last at home and he ran away, because once his father was mad at him and he didn't let him come into the house in the middle of winter, and he got pneumonia and almost died.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he decided he cannot stand this treatment, and there must be other ways to live.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he decided he'll go to Vienna, because that was the center of this silver and gold business.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when he got-- he really ran away, his mother knew about it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He bought himself some pants, he always told us, and-- and a warm jacket.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he bought a ticket to Krakow, where he was supposed to change trains for Vienna.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he missed the train for Vienna, and there was a train going to Prague.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So he decided one must be as good as the other, and he went to Prague.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And in Prague he-- it wasn't difficult for him to get a job, because people who very lived-- who knew how to do it, how to work, there were not many.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So he got a very good job, and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] started saving.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He lived-- he rented a room somewhere.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And I think he met somebody at the train station, a lady who spoke Yiddish or who looked Jewish.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And she gave him a name, and they rented him a room with-- with-- with board.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "He also made a vow never to go to a synagogue and never to eat kosher again.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Those were his decision for life, and he kept them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And he started to save.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And then came the war, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
